.TH "invalidate_inode_pages2" 9 "invalidate_inode_pages2" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
invalidate_inode_pages2 \- remove all pages from an address_space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" invalidate_inode_pages2
.BI "(struct address_space *mapping "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mapping" 12
the address_space
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Any pages which are found to be mapped into pagetables are unmapped prior to
invalidation.
.SH "RETURN"
-EBUSY if any pages could not be invalidated.
